{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":125221,"databundleVersionId":16856040,"isSourceIdPinned":false},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15604713,"datasetId":9945668,"databundleVersionId":16538098}],"dockerImageVersionId":31328,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"992a6b24-b32e-4f4a-8d99-5df4f4222b2d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 🏎️ Predicting F1 Pit Stops — v2: External Data + LGBM/XGB/CatBoost Ensemble\n**Playground S6E5** · Metric **ROC-AUC** · Target `PitNextLap`\n\n### What changed vs v1, and *why* (all decisions were A/B-tested on a held-out subsample)\n| Change | OOF effect in our test | Decision |\n|---|---|---|\n| Add **external real-F1 data** to training | **+0.0046** | ✅ keep — biggest lever |\n| Ensemble **LightGBM + XGBoost + CatBoost** (rank-avg) | model diversity | ✅ keep |\n| Seed-averaging LightGBM | variance reduction | ✅ keep |\n| Extra \"hazard\" target-encodings | −0.003 | ❌ dropped (a GBDT already learns those interactions) |\n| Extra lag/rolling features | −0.001 | ❌ dropped (noise) |\n\n**Lean features win.** v1's feature set already captured the signal; piling on more features hurt. v1 CV (StratifiedKFold) matched the LB to within 0.0005, so **trust the OOF AUC** printed below.\n\n> **Accelerator:** Runs on **CPU** fine (~30–45 min). To go faster, enable a **GPU (T4 x2 or P100)** in the notebook settings and set `USE_GPU = True` — that accelerates XGBoost and CatBoost.\n>\n> **⚠️ Add the external dataset:** In the notebook's *Input* panel, click **Add Input → Datasets**, search for the F1 strategy dataset (the `f1_strategy_dataset_v4.csv` you have), and add it. The load cell auto-detects common paths; if it can't find the file it will fall back to synthetic-only with a printed warning.","metadata":{}},{"id":"46fc39ec-6e2d-44d5-a659-15274844166f","cell_type":"code","source":"import os, gc, warnings, numpy as np, pandas as pd\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold\nfrom sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score\nfrom scipy.stats import rankdata\nimport lightgbm as lgb\n\nSEED       = 42\nN_SPLITS   = 5\nTARGET     = \"PitNextLap\"\nUSE_EXTERNAL = True    # append real-F1 rows to TRAINING folds (validated +~0.005 OOF)\nUSE_GPU      = False   # set True ONLY if you turned on a GPU accelerator\n\n# Optional models — notebook still works if a library is missing\ntry:\n    import xgboost as xgb; HAS_XGB = True\nexcept Exception as e:\n    HAS_XGB = False; print(\"XGBoost unavailable:\", e)\ntry:\n    from catboost import CatBoostClassifier; HAS_CAT = True\nexcept Exception as e:\n    HAS_CAT = False; print(\"CatBoost unavailable:\", e)\nprint(f\"LightGBM {lgb.__version__} | XGB={HAS_XGB} | CatBoost={HAS_CAT} | GPU={USE_GPU}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.536174Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.536864Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.545729Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.536794Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.544560Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"LightGBM 4.6.0 | XGB=True | CatBoost=True | GPU=False\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"90c71f15-7b7f-4045-a1ae-ba670abdc058","cell_type":"code","source":"# ---------- Load competition data ----------\nCAND = [\"/kaggle/input/playground-series-s6e5\",\n        \"/kaggle/input/competitions/playground-series-s6e5\", \".\"]\nBASE = next((p for p in CAND if os.path.exists(os.path.join(p,\"train.csv\"))), \".\")\nprint(\"competition data from:\", BASE)\ntrain  = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/train.csv\")\ntest   = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/test.csv\")\nsample = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/sample_submission.csv\")\nprint(\"train\", train.shape, \"| test\", test.shape)\n\n# ---------- Locate external real-F1 dataset (optional) ----------\next_raw = None\nif USE_EXTERNAL:\n    import glob\n    hits = glob.glob(\"/kaggle/input/datasets/aadigupta1601/f1-strategy-dataset-pit-stop-prediction/f1_strategy_dataset_v4.csv\", recursive=True) + \\\n           glob.glob(\"./f1_strategy_dataset*.csv\")\n    if hits:\n        ext_raw = pd.read_csv(hits[0]); print(\"external data from:\", hits[0], ext_raw.shape)\n    else:\n        print(\"⚠️ external dataset NOT found — proceeding synthetic-only. Add it via Add Input to enable the +0.005 boost.\")\n        USE_EXTERNAL = False","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.548904Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.549574Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T19:46:44.274625Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T19:46:42.549540Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T19:46:44.273360Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"competition data from: /kaggle/input/competitions/playground-series-s6e5\ntrain (439140, 16) | test (188165, 15)\nexternal data from: /kaggle/input/datasets/aadigupta1601/f1-strategy-dataset-pit-stop-prediction/f1_strategy_dataset_v4.csv (101371, 16)\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"295b16c9-734a-492b-92df-b9ba509f1e23","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Feature engineering (the proven v1 set) + priors\nPriors (expected stint length per compound, race length) are learned from the **synthetic train** only. The same `build_features` is applied to train, test, and the external data.","metadata":{}},{"id":"93800b83-c7e4-48cf-9324-219fc110d86e","cell_type":"code","source":"COMP_ORD = {\"SOFT\":0,\"MEDIUM\":1,\"HARD\":2,\"INTERMEDIATE\":3,\"WET\":4}\n\n_sl = (train.sort_values([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\",\"Stint\",\"LapNumber\"])\n            .groupby([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\",\"Stint\"])\n            .agg(slen=(\"TyreLife\",\"max\"), comp=(\"Compound\",\"first\")).reset_index())\nCOMP_STINT = _sl.groupby(\"comp\")[\"slen\"].mean().to_dict()\nRACE_LEN   = (pd.concat([train[[\"Race\",\"Year\",\"LapNumber\"]], test[[\"Race\",\"Year\",\"LapNumber\"]]])\n                .groupby([\"Race\",\"Year\"])[\"LapNumber\"].max().to_dict())\nRL_MED     = int(np.median(list(RACE_LEN.values())))\nprint(\"expected stint length by compound:\", {k:round(v,1) for k,v in COMP_STINT.items()})\n\ndef build_features(df):\n    df = df.copy()\n    df[\"Compound\"]        = df[\"Compound\"].fillna(\"MEDIUM\")\n    df[\"comp_ord\"]        = df[\"Compound\"].map(COMP_ORD).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"comp_exp_stint\"]  = df[\"Compound\"].map(COMP_STINT).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyre_life_ratio\"] = (df[\"TyreLife\"]/df[\"comp_exp_stint\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"race_len\"]        = df.set_index([\"Race\",\"Year\"]).index.map(RACE_LEN).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"race_len\"]        = df[\"race_len\"].fillna(RL_MED).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"laps_remaining\"]  = (df[\"race_len\"]-df[\"LapNumber\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"frac_remaining\"]  = (df[\"laps_remaining\"]/df[\"race_len\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"deg_per_lap\"]     = (df[\"Cumulative_Degradation\"]/(df[\"TyreLife\"]+1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyrelife_x_prog\"] = (df[\"TyreLife\"]*df[\"RaceProgress\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyrelife_x_ratio\"]= (df[\"TyreLife\"]*df[\"tyre_life_ratio\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"stint_x_tyrelife\"]= (df[\"Stint\"]*df[\"TyreLife\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"pos_norm\"]        = (df[\"Position\"]/20.0).astype(\"float32\")\n    df = df.sort_values([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\",\"LapNumber\"])\n    g  = df.groupby([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\"], sort=False); lt = df[\"LapTime (s)\"]\n    df[\"prev_pit\"]      = g[\"PitStop\"].shift(1)\n    df[\"laptime_chg\"]   = (lt - g[\"LapTime (s)\"].shift(1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyrelife_chg\"]  = (df[\"TyreLife\"] - g[\"TyreLife\"].shift(1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"deg_chg\"]       = (df[\"Cumulative_Degradation\"] - g[\"Cumulative_Degradation\"].shift(1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"laptime_vs_avg\"]= (lt - g[\"LapTime (s)\"].cumsum()/(g.cumcount()+1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    return df.reset_index(drop=True)\n\ntrain_fe = build_features(train)\ntest_fe  = build_features(test)\next_fe   = build_features(ext_raw) if USE_EXTERNAL else None\n\n# Race categorical code (shared mapping across train/test/ext)\nall_races = set(train[\"Race\"]) | set(test[\"Race\"])\nif USE_EXTERNAL: all_races |= set(ext_raw[\"Race\"])\nrace_cats = pd.CategoricalDtype(categories=sorted(all_races))\nfor d in [train_fe, test_fe] + ([ext_fe] if USE_EXTERNAL else []):\n    d[\"Race_cat\"] = d[\"Race\"].astype(race_cats).cat.codes.astype(\"int32\")\n\nNUM_FEATS = [\"comp_ord\",\"TyreLife\",\"Stint\",\"Position\",\"LapNumber\",\"RaceProgress\",\"Position_Change\",\n             \"LapTime (s)\",\"LapTime_Delta\",\"Cumulative_Degradation\",\"PitStop\",\"Year\",\n             \"comp_exp_stint\",\"tyre_life_ratio\",\"race_len\",\"laps_remaining\",\"frac_remaining\",\n             \"deg_per_lap\",\"tyrelife_x_prog\",\"tyrelife_x_ratio\",\"stint_x_tyrelife\",\"pos_norm\",\n             \"prev_pit\",\"laptime_chg\",\"tyrelife_chg\",\"deg_chg\",\"laptime_vs_avg\",\"Race_cat\"]\nFEATS = NUM_FEATS + [\"Driver_te\"]   # Driver_te added per-fold (leak-free)\nprint(len(FEATS), \"model features; external rows:\", 0 if ext_fe is None else len(ext_fe))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T19:46:44.276262Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T19:46:44.276739Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.244065Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T19:46:44.276706Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.243282Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"expected stint length by compound: {'HARD': 23.6, 'INTERMEDIATE': 17.2, 'MEDIUM': 17.9, 'SOFT': 14.3, 'WET': 13.8}\n29 model features; external rows: 101371\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"id":"93a0228c-e136-470b-ad9d-9437dffefd20","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Cross-validation + ensemble\nFor every fold: training = synthetic-train-fold **+ external data** (validation/test are always synthetic only). `Driver` target-encoding is fit on the training rows only. Three models are trained and their **rank-averaged** probabilities form the blend.","metadata":{}},{"id":"8f499f11-1657-44ec-9946-b0625605b1a8","cell_type":"code","source":"def smoothed_te(frame, cat, target, m=50.0):\n    # Driver target-encoding fit on training rows only (leak-free).\n    glob = frame[target].mean()\n    agg  = frame.groupby(cat)[target].agg([\"mean\",\"count\"])\n    enc  = ((agg[\"mean\"]*agg[\"count\"] + glob*m)/(agg[\"count\"]+m)).to_dict()\n    return enc, glob\n\ndef fit_lgb(Xtr,ytr,Xva,yva,Xte,seeds=(42,2024)):\n    vp=np.zeros(len(yva)); tp=np.zeros(len(Xte))\n    for s in seeds:\n        params=dict(objective=\"binary\",metric=\"auc\",learning_rate=0.02,num_leaves=256,\n                    feature_fraction=0.7,bagging_fraction=0.8,bagging_freq=1,min_child_samples=60,\n                    lambda_l1=1.0,lambda_l2=2.0,max_bin=255,verbose=-1,n_jobs=-1,seed=s)\n        m=lgb.train(params,lgb.Dataset(Xtr,ytr),num_boost_round=6000,\n                    valid_sets=[lgb.Dataset(Xva,yva)],\n                    callbacks=[lgb.early_stopping(150),lgb.log_evaluation(0)])\n        vp+=m.predict(Xva)/len(seeds); tp+=m.predict(Xte)/len(seeds)\n    return vp,tp\n\ndef fit_xgb(Xtr,ytr,Xva,yva,Xte):\n    dtr=xgb.DMatrix(Xtr,label=ytr); dva=xgb.DMatrix(Xva,label=yva); dte=xgb.DMatrix(Xte)\n    params={\"objective\":\"binary:logistic\",\"eval_metric\":\"auc\",\"eta\":0.02,\"max_depth\":8,\n            \"subsample\":0.8,\"colsample_bytree\":0.7,\"min_child_weight\":5,\n            \"reg_lambda\":2.0,\"reg_alpha\":1.0,\"tree_method\":\"hist\",\"seed\":SEED}\n    if USE_GPU: params[\"device\"]=\"cuda\"\n    m=xgb.train(params,dtr,num_boost_round=6000,evals=[(dva,\"v\")],\n                early_stopping_rounds=150,verbose_eval=False)\n    rng=(0,m.best_iteration+1)\n    return m.predict(dva,iteration_range=rng), m.predict(dte,iteration_range=rng)\n\ndef fit_cat(Xtr,ytr,Xva,yva,Xte):\n    m=CatBoostClassifier(iterations=6000,learning_rate=0.03,depth=8,l2_leaf_reg=3.0,\n        loss_function=\"Logloss\",eval_metric=\"AUC\",random_seed=SEED,\n        task_type=(\"GPU\" if USE_GPU else \"CPU\"),verbose=False,early_stopping_rounds=150)\n    m.fit(Xtr,ytr,eval_set=(Xva,yva),use_best_model=True)\n    return m.predict_proba(Xva)[:,1], m.predict_proba(Xte)[:,1]","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.245412Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.245793Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.258163Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.245763Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.257240Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":9},{"id":"84ebab7a-fd6e-4d0e-9f89-8167889d694e","cell_type":"code","source":"y   = train_fe[TARGET].values.astype(\"int8\")\nnte = len(test_fe)\noof  = {k:np.zeros(len(train_fe)) for k in [\"lgb\",\"xgb\",\"cat\"]}\npred = {k:np.zeros(nte)            for k in [\"lgb\",\"xgb\",\"cat\"]}\nused = {\"lgb\":True, \"xgb\":HAS_XGB, \"cat\":HAS_CAT}\n\nskf=StratifiedKFold(n_splits=N_SPLITS, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED)\nfor fold,(tri,vai) in enumerate(skf.split(train_fe,y)):\n    tr_syn = train_fe.iloc[tri]\n    tr_all = pd.concat([tr_syn, ext_fe], ignore_index=True) if (USE_EXTERNAL and ext_fe is not None) else tr_syn\n    ytr = tr_all[TARGET].values.astype(\"int8\")\n    enc,glob = smoothed_te(tr_all,\"Driver\",TARGET,m=50.0)\n    def mat(frame):\n        X = frame[NUM_FEATS].copy()\n        X[\"Driver_te\"] = frame[\"Driver\"].map(enc).fillna(glob).values.astype(\"float32\")\n        return X\n    Xtr=mat(tr_all); Xva=mat(train_fe.iloc[vai]); Xte=mat(test_fe); yva=y[vai]\n    vp,tp=fit_lgb(Xtr.values,ytr,Xva.values,yva,Xte.values); oof[\"lgb\"][vai]=vp; pred[\"lgb\"]+=tp/N_SPLITS\n    if HAS_XGB:\n        vp,tp=fit_xgb(Xtr.values,ytr,Xva.values,yva,Xte.values); oof[\"xgb\"][vai]=vp; pred[\"xgb\"]+=tp/N_SPLITS\n    if HAS_CAT:\n        vp,tp=fit_cat(Xtr.values,ytr,Xva.values,yva,Xte.values); oof[\"cat\"][vai]=vp; pred[\"cat\"]+=tp/N_SPLITS\n    msg=\" | \".join(f\"{k}={roc_auc_score(yva,oof[k][vai]):.5f}\" for k in [\"lgb\",\"xgb\",\"cat\"] if used[k])\n    print(f\"fold {fold+1}: {msg}\", flush=True)\n    del Xtr,Xva,Xte,tr_all; gc.collect()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.260051Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T19:46:46.260471Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Training until validation scores don't improve for 150 rounds\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":null},{"id":"195881f8-a760-4dfc-b23e-a32fa189360a","cell_type":"code","source":"def rb(a): return rankdata(a)/len(a)\nmodels=[k for k in [\"lgb\",\"xgb\",\"cat\"] if used[k]]\nprint(\"Per-model OOF AUC:\")\nfor k in models: print(f\"   {k}: {roc_auc_score(y,oof[k]):.5f}\")\noof_blend = np.mean([rb(oof[k]) for k in models], axis=0)\noof_mean  = np.mean([oof[k]     for k in models], axis=0)\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*46)\nprint(f\"  RANK-BLEND OOF AUC = {roc_auc_score(y,oof_blend):.5f}\")\nprint(f\"  mean-blend OOF AUC = {roc_auc_score(y,oof_mean):.5f}\")\nprint(\"=\"*46)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"dd6abb00-b0bf-4646-a54b-42a33ab566fd","cell_type":"code","source":"# ---- Submission from rank-blended test predictions (id-aligned) ----\npred_blend = np.mean([rb(pred[k]) for k in models], axis=0)\npred_df = pd.DataFrame({\"id\": test_fe[\"id\"].values, TARGET: pred_blend})\nsample2 = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/sample_submission.csv\")\nsubmission = sample2[[\"id\"]].merge(pred_df, on=\"id\", how=\"left\")\nassert submission[TARGET].isna().sum()==0 and (submission[\"id\"].values==sample2[\"id\"].values).all()\nsubmission.to_csv(\"submission.csv\", index=False)\nprint(\"saved submission.csv\", submission.shape, \"| id order verified\")\nprint(submission.head())","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"452e24f0-8434-4eeb-97e5-077b63c914aa","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Next steps\n1. **Report the per-model + blend OOF AUC, and the LB after submitting.** Blend OOF should beat v1's 0.9493.\n2. If one model lags badly, drop it from the blend or down-weight it.\n3. **Optuna tuning** of LightGBM/XGB depth & regularization, then re-blend.\n4. Try **GroupKFold(Driver×Race)** as a robustness check that CV still tracks LB.\n5. More **seeds** for XGB/CatBoost (currently single-seed) once we know each helps.","metadata":{}}]}